armistice /ˈɑːmɪstɪs/

N-SING An armistice is an agreement between countries who are at war with one another to stop fighting and to discuss ways of making peace. 停火协议; 停战协议 

例： Finally, the Bolsheviks signed an armistice with Germany. 布尔什维克最终与德国签署了停战协议。

